    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Dvalin",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "In ancient times, when the gods in their prime walked among the people, the elemental dragon graced by Anemo was born in the high heavens in that age of wonders. Elemental dragons are rarely seen and have the powers to match the gods of old. The high dragon slowly descended and inspected everything with curious eyes. He landed in a village, but the terrified villagers threw rocks at him. The dragon could not understand why they cried out in fear. He landed in a cemetery and only heard the lament of grieving people. The dragon was perplexed as to the reason for their sorrowful murmurs. He landed in an orchard but was cursed by the furious farmers who lost their trees. The dragon couldn't figure out why they yelled in fury. The world was too complicated for a young dragon. The dragon was bewildered, yet he did not give up. One day, the dragon heard music pouring out from the Holy Lyre der Himmel. This was the name of the lyre belonging to the Anemo Archon. Enchanted by the poetry, the Wind Dragon landed beside the best singer under the skies. People panicked, for the mighty elemental dragons and the great archons that reigned over the earth had never seen eye to eye.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Behold his beauty and benignity!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Windborne Bard sang.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"But we do not know him,\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "the people replied.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/e4000b2c075772f202082c9a2c15c847_7839965773653386895.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "A mysterious magic lies behind the music and poetry, which has the power to mesmerize both dragons and humans. The dragon decided to stay with the bard, for he, too, wished to be understood by all souls. He learned human speech and the Windborne Bard's singing techniques. That's how the friendship between the high dragon Dvalin and Anemo Archon Barbatos began. Barbatos rejoiced in making a new friend and entrusted the people of Mondstadt to Dvalin.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "When Barbatos and the slave Vennessa overthrew the Aristocracy of Mondstadt and Vennessa founded the Knights of Favonius to rule the people, she also summoned the Four Winds to protect Mondstadt. Dvalin became the Dragon of the East, and the people of Mondstadt worshiped him and other protectors for generations.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3796,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/04/26/169177528/a19531bd8e93b793b79bfe1499b5b5d7_1821424930343002645.png",
                      "name": "Mondstadt",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7084,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/11/17/237301566/93cd2bc9b90c8b87b1f8cbdbe95b4b9d_6244634971554940377.png",
                      "menu_id": 23,
                      "name": "Elemental Dragons",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7432,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/01/14/237301566/93cd2bc9b90c8b87b1f8cbdbe95b4b9d_3415618910255857517.png",
                      "menu_id": 23,
                      "name": "Four Winds",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7468,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/02/25/237301566/5f7d70114271f8eca21f24cd62499dc6_6114532498612516105.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Barbatos",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4901,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Vennessa",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2318,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/book/Breeze Amidst the Forest_icon.png",
                      "name": "Breeze Amidst the Forest",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3800,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/05/08/77454259/59425415f62733a7a83dab22c5787b19_8211155150467748760.png",
                      "name": "Holy Lyre der Himmel",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Stormterror",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/25dc69c3876ff2d171c7b1aac166ca3a_2860172354413886056.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "500 years ago, the Eclipse Dynasty of the Khaenri'ah Kingdom fell. An alchemist named Gold, corrupted by her own greed and ambition, created an army of shadowy monsters with their uncanny powers that filled all seven kingdoms of Teyvat. These were particularly difficult times for Mondstadt. The Lionfang Knight was without a suitable heir, and the Knights of Favonius had lost many of their brave men and women during the bitter wars. The black serpent-dragon Durin was one of the \"children\" of the alchemist Rhinedottir, who rose from the sea, casting his shadow over Mondstadt. The people of Mondstadt believed that he wanted to destroy all living things. The envy of the devilish dragon gave rise to evil that poisoned the land and the people who lived on it. In those terrible days, bloodthirsty monsters and desolation came to Mondstadt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/3dd966675be0cb2d46c420ae09c0bf6d_657516347791093780.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Awoken from his sylvan slumber by the cries of Durin's victims, the Anemo Archon came forth and summoned his faithful servant to his side. For life and for freedom, the Archon and the Wind Dragon rode the wind to face their foe. In a battle that ripped clouds from the skies, Dvalin spread his six blessed wings wide, severing the sky and tearing through Durin's iron scales with the force of a colossal blade. As the conflict plunged the world into darkness, the Wind Dragon struck out with his claws, like swords forged of wind, and they pierced deep into Durin's dark, corrupt flesh. The battle shook the heavens; even the sun quaked with fear. Finally, Dvalin tore out Durin's throat with his teeth, and the evil dragon fell from the sky.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/6c0fdabd2b5888ea057483852a685038_3779718316371348031.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "With his god's blessing, the Wind Dragon seized victory and saved the people of Mondstadt. Durin's body fell into the ruins of the ancient kingdom of Sal Vindagnyr, which has since been called the Dragonspine. Dvalin himself inadvertently swallowed Durin's poisonous blood, and it slowly poisoned his body to the marrow of his bones. The dragon lost consciousness from unbearable pain, and no one knew where Dvalin fell.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Should you awaken, spread your wings, and live your life freely! A dragon is born to soar the skies, and mortals shall surely grasp your beauty.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "People used to believe that Dvalin would awaken whenever Mondstadt faced a new threat. But in these times of peace, the belief in the Four Winds has gradually eroded, and their temples lie all but completely deserted. In the century while Dvalin slept, his image faded from Mondstadt's memory.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/f1098093d99b6d155aa588d664021eb1_1063811694369280333.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Awakening from a hundred-year sleep from the poison corroding his body, Dvalin did not hear the singing of the lyre of his faithful friend. He believed that Barbatos had betrayed and abandoned him. Now the people he once protected have fled from him. Deceived by the Abyss, the Wind Dragon fell to evil, and Stormterror was born. He settled in the ruins of Old Mondstadt, where the tyrant Decarabian ruled more than two thousand years ago. This place became known as the Stormterror's Lair.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/20/237301566/48e5ede86050b7eec8728ad8c567e909_4296986223407355424.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Centuries later, Anemo Archon awoke from his sleep to find his friend in rage and anguish. At that time, Dvalin was controlled by the Abyss mage, whispering to him about the betrayal of Barbatos and the people of Mondstadt. With the help of the Traveler, Barbatos was able to heal Dvalin and clear the poison from his mind. Barbatos granted the dragon the blessing of Anemo Archon, and the six-winged high dragon finally remembered his friend. He asked Anemo Archon why he did not order him to protect the people, to which Barbatos replied:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Freedom, if demanded of you by an Archon. Is really no freedom at all.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Riding on the boundless winds, Dvalin took to the skies once again.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
